The paper proposes a learnable framework for propagating visual properties of video images, which involves modeling the transition-related affinity between frames. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper proposes a data-driven approach that involves regularizing a global transformation matrix, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also deals with video processing, which suggests that it may belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Furthermore, the paper involves modeling and propagating segmentation masks, which suggests that it may belong to the graphics (cs.GR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of a switchable TPN, which suggests that it may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
